            <title>[HIVE-12605] Implement JDBC Connection.isValid</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-12605</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/sql/Connection.html#isValid(int&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/sql/Connection.html#isValid(int&lt;/a&gt;) implementation in Hive JDBC driver throws &quot;SQLException(&quot;Method not supported&quot;)&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That is a method often used by connection pooling libraries.&lt;/p&gt;

