                            <comment id="15045292" author="thejas" created="Mon, 7 Dec 2015 17:26:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The javadoc for the JDBC api says - &quot;The driver shall submit a query on the connection or use some other mechanism that positively verifies the connection is still valid when this method is called. &quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We could use something lightweight &apos;read&apos; operation to validate the connection. Maybe a &apos;set &amp;lt;config name&amp;gt;&apos; , where it just prints the value of the config name.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15063306" author="gliptak" created="Fri, 18 Dec 2015 02:23:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=thejas&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;thejas&quot;&gt;thejas&lt;/a&gt; Would this be a good approach? Thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15063421" author="thejas" created="Fri, 18 Dec 2015 04:27:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=gliptak&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;gliptak&quot;&gt;gliptak&lt;/a&gt; I think that&apos;s a great approach!&lt;br/&gt;
Can you also please add unit tests ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
